def: An Australian insessorial bird (Corcorax melanorhamphus) notedfor the curious actions of the male during the breeding season. It isblack with a white patch on each wing.
The tough, fibrous membrane, which lines the cavity of theskull and spinal column, and surrounds the brain and spinal cord; --frequently abbreviated to dura.
Any marine annelid of the genus Hyalin√¶cia, especially H.tubicola of Europe, which inhabits a transparent movable tuberesembling a quill in color and texture.
Capable of being cleared off, as a debt.

The internal ear. See Note under Ear.
To form a boll or seed vessel; to go to seed.The barley was in the ear, and the flax was bolled. Ex. ix. 31.
